author: sun-sentinel.com
title: Eight Games Moved to Thursday Palm Beach - Sun Sentinel
text:
Eight Palm Beach football games previously scheduled for Friday have been moved to Thursday because of Teacher Plan Day across the county.
Jupiter at Palm Beach Central, Wellington at Palm Beach Gardens, John I. Leonard at Boca Raton, Santaluces at Spanish River, West Boca at Dwyer, Royal Palm Beach at Olympic Heights and Boynton Beach at Suncoast will all be played at 7 p.m. on Thursday.
The only game with a time change is Lake Worth at Atlantic, which is now scheduled for 6 p.m.
There are still 12 games involving Palm Beach schools scheduled for Friday.
